{"label":"Parts of speech-3","id":"parts-of-speech-3","list":[{"id":"well","label":"Well","type":"classifySentence","data":{"title":"Indentify the parts of speech of the underlined word.","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"Are you *well*?\nShe is *well*.\nMy grandmother is doing *well*. "},{"name":"Adverb","text":"She paints very *well*."},{"name":"Noun","text":"I dropped a coin in the *well*. \nThey dig a *well* to get water out of the ground.\nI went down to the *well* to get some water. \nThe dog jumped into the *well*."},{"name":"Interjection","text":"*Well*! That's expensive!\n*Well*! That’s huge!"}]}},{"label":"Identify the Parts of Speech","type":"classifySentence","id":"classify","commonData":{"title":"Identify the parts of speech of the underlined word."},"data":[{"microLabel":"brick","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"I live in a *brick* house."},{"name":"Noun","text":"My house is made of *bricks*.\nThis wall is made of *bricks*.\nThis tiny garden is surrounded by high *brick* walls.\nShe built the bookshelves using *bricks*."}]},{"microLabel":"call","types":[{"name":"Verb","text":"Please *call* your mother.\nWould you *call* me as soon as you find out. \nMy friend gave me this number to *call*."},{"name":"Noun","text":"He received a *call* at work.\nI received a *call* from my brother last night.\nI *called* him by his nickname.\nI have had hundreds of *calls* from parents."}]},{"microLabel":"car","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"He drives an old *car*.\nThey arrived by *car*.\nShe bought a new *car*.\nI’ll wait in the *car*."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"My brother works for a *car* dealership."}]},{"microLabel":"judge","types":[{"name":"Verb","text":"Mr. Bhaskar will *judge* the final round.\nWe asked Madhu to *judge* the art show.\nI *judged* her age to be around thirty years."},{"name":"Noun","text":"The *judge* sentenced the criminal to life in prison.\nA panel of *judges* are selecting the players.\n*Judge* Mr. Patnaik jailed him for life."}]},{"microLabel":"little","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"That *little* cat makes a lot of noise.\nThis puppy has *little* feet.\nMy friend had *little* money left.\nThere is *little* scope for new fields in India.\nThere is *little* danger in slides than in swings."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"My son eats very *little*.\nThis is a *little* known fact. \nShe walked a *little* by herself in the garden.\nShe was a *little* bit afraid of her mother’s reaction.\nShe talks very *little*.\nHe eats very *little*."}]},{"microLabel":"play","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"My daughter was an actor in a *play*.\nShe wrote, directed and starred in a *play*.\nThe *play* is based on real-life events."},{"name":"Verb","text":"Most of the children like to *play* cricket.\nI used to *play* basketball.\nWest Indies will *play* against India."}]},{"microLabel":"rich","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"The *rich* have many friends.\nThere is hunger in many parts of the world, even in *rich* countries."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"A *rich* country has a good economy.\nYou are going to be a very *rich* man.\nFish is a *rich* source of protein"}]},{"microLabel":"stamp","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"Give me a *stamp*.\nIt’s a free post, so a *stamp* is not required. \nI bought a few *stamps*."},{"name":"verb","text":"*Stamp* this envelope.\nBike manufacturers *stamp* a vehicle identification number in many places."}]},{"microLabel":"fast","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"*Fast* cars with flashing lights and sirens.\nThis is a *fast* boat.\nHe is a very *fast* runner."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"The snow is melting *fast*.\nShe works terrifically *fast*.\nHow *fast* were you riding?"}]},{"microLabel":"straight","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"Keep the boat in *straight* line.\nHer hair is *straight*."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"The arrow flew *straight*. \nThe ball fell *straight* into the hands of the fielder. \nHe came *straight* home from work."}]}]},{"label":"Identify - 2","type":"classifySentence","id":"classify-2","commonData":{"title":"Identify the parts of speech of the underlined word."},"data":[{"microLabel":"work","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"I went to *work*.\nWhat kind of *work* do you do?\nMy *work* is hard. \nI am still looking for *work*."},{"name":"Verb","text":"Where do you *work*?\nHe *worked* all day in the garden. \nThe door hinges *work* better with oil. \nI *work* in Mumbai."}]},{"microLabel":"answer","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"The *answer* to question 4 is A.\nHer *answer* surprised us.\nHis only *answer* was to walk out."},{"name":"Verb","text":"*Answer* my question, please.\nShe must *answer* for her crimes."}]},{"microLabel":"hard","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"He hit his head on the *hard* ground.\nI paid in *hard* cash.\nIt’s a *hard* mattress."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"I’ll work *hard*. \nWe have worked *hard* all day.\nI studied *hard* for my exams, but it didn’t go well."}]},{"microLabel":"down","types":[{"name":"Preposition","text":"We are going *down* a mountain. \nKindly write *down* the phone number.\nThe ball rolled *down* the road."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"The old man sounded really *down*. \nMy laptop is *down*. \nMy brother is *down* with the flu."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"Don’t look *down*. \nPlease sit *down*. \nThe kitten fell *down*."},{"name":"Noun","text":"Everyone has ups and *downs* in life."}]},{"microLabel":"before","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"She has never been to England *before*.\nI have seen this *before*."},{"name":"Preposition","text":"Mihira was born a few weeks *before* Christmas. \nI like to go for a walk *before* breakfast."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"He went away *before* I came. \nCan you call me *before* you go? \nPlease get out of here *before* I call the police."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"He came *before* time."}]},{"microLabel":"better","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"They liked it *better* when it rained.\nHe dances *better* than me.\nMy mom knows *better*."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"The weather is *better* today than it was yesterday. \nShe is a *better* singer than I am. \nHe came up with a *better* solution to the problem. \nShe has a *better* plan."}]},{"microLabel":"except","types":[{"name":"Preposition","text":"The stores will be open daily *except* Sundays. \nEveryone was invited *except* me.\nShe likes everyone *except* you."},{"name":"Verb","text":"*Except* Hari, all are to be blamed."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"Nothing more to do now, *except* wait."}]},{"microLabel":"less","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"We are eating more and exercising *less*.\nPoverty is *less* of a problem now than it used to be.\nThe red jacket is *less* expensive.\nThe population of India is *less* than China.\nThe train is *less* riskier than a plane.\nWater in rivers is *less* than that in the oceans."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"You are paying *less* attention to your studies than you used to do.\nYou’re paying *less* attention to your studies.\nSaanvi has *less* interest in household work.\nRohit is *less* efficient for this job."},{"name":"Noun","text":"He won’t settle for *less*."}]},{"microLabel":"near","types":[{"name":"Preposition","text":"Don’t come *near* me.\nI lived *near* the school.\nShe walks *near* the park.\nHis school is *near* the railway station.\nShe walks *near* the park.\nHis school is *near* the railway station."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"She took a step *nearer* to the barrier. \nCome *nearer*, I’ll tell you a story."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"Where is the *nearest* phone?\nI frequently meet people *near* me.\nI have a good friendship with my *near* cousin."}]},{"microLabel":"once","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"Lung cells die and are replaced *once* a week.\nI went paragliding *once*.\nShe rode a horse only *once*.\nMy son comes to visit me *once* every fortnight."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"*Once* she spoke, I recognized her.\n*Once* you get there, you will love it."}]}]},{"label":"Identify - 3","type":"classifySentence","id":"classify-3","commonData":{"title":"Identify the parts of speech of the underlined word."},"data":[{"microLabel":"any","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"Have you got *any* books?\n*Any* movies you can suggest?\nYou can find water bottles in almost *any* shop."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"Is he *any* better?\nAre you good at *any* writing styles?\nI can’t do *any* sit-ups. I hate working out."}]},{"microLabel":"as","types":[{"name":"Conjunction","text":"*As* he was stuck in traffic, he got late.\nShe immediately left *as* I came.\n*As* the bell rang, we switched off the TV."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"She called *as* fast *as* she could.\nThe room was *as* warm *as* the sun.\nRahul is *as* smart *as* Sheena."}]},{"microLabel":"yet","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"There’s more food *yet* to be eaten.\nMy mom is *yet* to cook.\nI’m *yet* to get ready."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"She is busy, *yet* will come.\nShe hasn’t completed her HW, *yet* sleeping."}]},{"microLabel":"what","types":[{"name":"Interjection","text":"*What* a match!\n*What!* Really?\n*What* a dress!"},{"name":"Pronoun","text":"Give me *what* you can.\nShe said *what* she said.\nThat’s *what* is true."}]},{"microLabel":"up","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"Prices are *up*.\nI have pulled *up* my socks."},{"name":"Preposition","text":"We all face *ups* and downs.\nMonkeys can climb *up* very fast."},{"name":"Noun","text":"Let us go *up* the stairs."}]},{"microLabel":"such","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"Your room is *such* a mess.\nShe is *such* a pretty girl.\nMauli is *such* a liar."},{"name":"Pronoun","text":"*Such* was not my idea.\nI would never do anything as *such*."}]},{"microLabel":"still","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"Germs grow in *still* water.\nThe wind was *still*."},{"name":"Noun","text":"Slightest noise can be heard in the *still* of the night."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"He is *still* in class.\nShe is standing *still*.\nAre you *still* listening?"}]},{"microLabel":"so","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"I’m *so* sorry.\nI’m *so* happy.\nIt can be done *so* easily."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"They saw a poor man, *so* they gave him food.\nThere was no bed, *so* I slept on the floor.\nThe service wasn’t good *so* I left."}]},{"microLabel":"only","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"It was her *only* skirt.\nThat’s the *only* pair of heels I have."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"She was *only* stupid.\nHe is the *only* smart person in the room."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"Take what you want, *only* let me go.\nShe is good, *only* not in sports."}]},{"microLabel":"one","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"*One* day I’ll go to London.\nHe has only *one* pen.\nI have *one* brother."},{"name":"Pronoun","text":"The little *ones* are playing.\n*Ones* with an i-card will not be punished."},{"name":"Noun","text":"*One* can only imagine.\nHe is the *one* for me.\nShe is my favorite *one*."}]}]},{"label":"Identify - 4","type":"classifySentence","id":"classify-4","commonData":{"title":"Identify the parts of speech of the underlined word."},"data":[{"microLabel":"both","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"You cannot have it *both* ways.\n*Both* answers are correct.\nI can’t take *both* sides."},{"name":"Pronoun","text":"*Both* of them are asleep.\nYou *both* should behave yourselves.\nThese are *both* mine."}]},{"microLabel":"either","types":[{"name":"Pronoun","text":"Call *either* of your parents.\nI will punish *either* of you.\n*Either* person is wrong."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"She *either* watches TV or plays.\nMy brother is awake and I can’t sleep *either.*\nWe can *either* wait or go to the park."}]},{"microLabel":"else","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"She lives somewhere *else* now.\nI can’t trust anyone *else* for the job.\nIs there someone *else* in the hall with you?"},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"Hurry! *Else* you’ll be late.\nComplete your HW, *else* the teacher will punish you."}]},{"microLabel":"enough","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"I’ve had *enough*.\nThis isn’t *enough*. You must make more."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"You know the situation well *enough*.\nWe have *enough* pie for everyone."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"The movie wasn’t good *enough.*"}]},{"microLabel":"even","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"The chances are *even*.\nLet’s call it *even*."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"Does she *even* realize her mistake?\nHe is not *even* sorry."}]},{"microLabel":"like","types":[{"name":"Preposition","text":"Don’t walk *like* that.\nShe talks *like* her mother.\nHe climbs *like* a monkey."},{"name":"Noun","text":"You will never have my *like* for this photo."},{"name":"Verb","text":"I *like* my best friend a lot.\nI *like* tap dance.\nI *like* meeting new people."}]},{"microLabel":"more","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"We want *more* volunteers like her.\nI need *more* pens."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"You should talk less and act *more*."}]},{"microLabel":"much","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"There is *much* sense in this idea.\nMy book is *much* better than hers."},{"name":"Pronoun","text":"*Much* of it isn’t wrong."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"She sleeps too *much*.\nI like sandwiches very *much*."}]},{"microLabel":"neither","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"*Neither* of her stories are true.\n*Neither* sides are safe."},{"name":"Pronoun","text":"This pen belongs to *neither*."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"She *neither* eat nor let others eat."}]},{"microLabel":"next","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"I shall go to Mumbai *next* month.\n*Next* week, our exams are starting."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"What *next?*"},{"name":"Preposition","text":"My classroom is *next* to yours.\nThe teacher was walking *next* to me."}]},{"microLabel":"why","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"I know *why* he wrote it.\n*Why* did she sleep on the sofa?"},{"name":"Interjection","text":"That’s *why!*\n*Why* is it always you!"},{"name":"Noun","text":"Don’t focus on *why* right now.\nThis is *why* I prefer the train."}]}]},{"label":"Identify - 5","type":"classifySentence","id":"classify-5","commonData":{"title":"Identify the parts of speech of the underlined word."},"data":[{"microLabel":"while","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"Sit and rest for a *while*.\nTry sleeping for a *while*."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"*While* she was coming, I took a quick nap."}]},{"microLabel":"till","types":[{"name":"Conjunction","text":"Don’t start *till* the shots are fired.\nShe was on the track *till* the end."},{"name":"Preposition","text":"Don’t skip homework, we have time *till* Tuesday only."}]},{"microLabel":"that","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"What is *that* noise?\nIs *that* voice yours?"},{"name":"Pronoun","text":"I want a dress just like *that*.\n*That* is very similar to my dog’s belt."},{"name":"Conjunction","text":"He is studying so *that* he can play.\nShe is running so *that* she can lose weight."}]},{"microLabel":"some","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"we must find *some* solution to this."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"There were *some* twenty pens.\n*Some* people were missing after the disaster."}]},{"microLabel":"right","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"We must be aware of our *rights*.\nAll citizens have the *right* to information."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"A *right* teacher is very important in playschool.\nHe is the *right* person for the job."}]},{"microLabel":"wrong","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"*Wrong* doers never win.\nThis is *wrong*."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"You have chosen the *wrong* path.\nThis is the *wrong* classroom."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"Children often do the calculations *wrong.*\nI often spell words *wrong*."}]},{"microLabel":"over","types":[{"name":"Adverb","text":"Read it *over*.\nDo it all *over* again."},{"name":"Noun","text":"There are 20 *overs* in a T20 match.\nThere are 6 balls in an *over*."},{"name":"Preposition","text":"The cat climbed *over* the stool.\nIf I run faster, I can jump *over* this wall."}]},{"microLabel":"since","types":[{"name":"Preposition","text":"I haven’t slept *since* yesterday.\nWe shouldn’t use mobile in the dark *since* it is harmful to the eyes."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"I haven’t slept *since*.\nI haven’t seen her *since*."}]},{"microLabel":"round","types":[{"name":"Adjective","text":"The earth is *round*.\nMy dad went to a *round* table conference."},{"name":"Preposition","text":"The boy ran *round* the tree.\nI put thread all *round* the table."},{"name":"Noun","text":"It was just the first *round*.\nIt’s the final *round* of the game."}]},{"microLabel":"back","types":[{"name":"Noun","text":"She stabbed me in the *back*.\nI have *back* pain."},{"name":"Adverb","text":"I will come *back* soon.\nShe’s going *back* to her farmhouse."},{"name":"Adjective","text":"Have you seen my *back* pack?\nWe have a *back* door but we don’t use it."},{"name":"Verb","text":"She’s *back!*\nI’m *backing* the car, please guide me."}]}]}]}